The Event IWD Techstars virtual event will be moderated by Christina Soname, VP of Learning & Development at Revent Academy. The virtual event themed “IWD TechStars: On powering their personal journeys to leadership roles in technology” is aimed at promoting the capabilities of African women in tech careers by highlighting the stories of high achieving women. The line-up of speakers will seek to inspire women to challenge societal biases that may stop them from pursuing careers of their choice. Speakers Speaking about the event, Babatola Awe, Co-founder, and CEO of  Revent Technologies stated that women hold the key to unlocking limitless possibilities for organizations and indeed the world at large. “IWD TechStars event is an expression of our corporate philosophy of creating an environment where women can thrive. Our list of speakers is a terrific inspiration to young women across the world and our attendees will gain so much from their journeys to leadership positions in the technology space.” He added. Revent Technologies’s IWD TechStars event will bring women together and inspire them using true stories from people who have ‘done it’. Date: Wednesday, 9th March Platform: Revent Technologies – Twitter Spaces Time: 2:30 p.m. The IWD Techstars event is powered by Revent Technologies, a leading ICT firm with expertise across Software Engineering, Digital Banking Solutions, Product Design, Technology Advisory, Outsourcing, Managed Service, Process Re-engineering and Automation, IoT & Cloud Solutions, Analytics & Cloud Solutions, Training. The post IWD TechStars: Revent Technologies Wants Women to Challenge Career Stereotypes appeared first on TechEconomy.ng. Receive top breaking news, events, ideas, and more!